<item>
            <title>[MATH-1067] Stack overflow in Beta.regularizedBeta</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/MATH-1067</link>
                <project id="12310485" key="MATH">Commons Math</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;In org.apache.commons.math3.special.Beta.regularizedBeta(double,double,double,double,int), the case&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; } else if (x &amp;gt; (a + 1.0) / (a + b + 2.0)) {&lt;br/&gt;
      ret = 1.0 - regularizedBeta(1.0 - x, b, a, epsilon, maxIterations);&lt;br/&gt;
} &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;is prone to infinite recursion: If x is approximately the tested value, then 1-x is approximately the tested value in the recursion. Thus, due to loss of precision after the subtraction, this condition can be true for the recursive call as well.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Example:&lt;br/&gt;
double x= Double.longBitsToDouble(4597303555101269224L);&lt;br/&gt;
double a= Double.longBitsToDouble(4634227472812299606L);&lt;br/&gt;
double b = Double.longBitsToDouble(4642050131540049920L);&lt;br/&gt;
System.out.println(x &amp;gt; (a + 1.0) / (a + b + 2.0));&lt;br/&gt;
System.out.println(1-x&amp;gt;(b + 1.0) / (b + a + 2.0));&lt;br/&gt;
System.out.println(1-(1-x)&amp;gt;(a + 1.0) / (a + b + 2.0));&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Possible solution: change the condition to&lt;br/&gt;
x &amp;gt; (a + 1.0) / (a + b + 2.0) &amp;amp;&amp;amp; 1-x&amp;lt;=(b + 1.0) / (b + a + 2.0)&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>&lt;p&gt;Java build 1.7.0_45-b18&lt;/p&gt;</environment>
